What are Hemostats and Sealants?
Hemostats and Sealants encompass a broad array of medical products designed to control bleeding and enhance wound healing during surgical procedures. These substances are used extensively in surgeries, trauma cases, and emergency care to provide rapid hemostasis either by physically sealing wounds or chemically enhancing clotting mechanisms. Hemostats include agents that facilitate blood clot formation by promoting platelet aggregation, while sealants are typically adhesive substances that close surgical incisions or lacerations by creating a physical barrier. These products are critical in both open and minimally invasive surgeries across various medical fields, such as cardiovascular, orthopedic, neurological, and general surgery.
Marketed under various proprietary brands by industry leaders, these products are applied through multiple methods and are currently standard of care in operating rooms across North America, Europe, and Asia-Pacific, establishing them as indispensable tools in modern surgical practice.
